<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07922</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT TO INCREASE THE UNCONDITIONAL CASH TRANSFER (UCT) PROGRAM TO P500.00 TO BENEFIT 22 MILLION POOR FILIPINOS, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates the DSWD to increase the Unconditional Cash Transfer from P200 to P500 to promote poverty alleviation schemes in a successive and progressive manner.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMERO, MICHAEL ODYLON L., Ph.D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-09-04)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>